<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870205-0078 </DOCNO><HL> Litton Gets $20 Million Job</HL><DD> 02/05/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LIT GM </IN><DATELINE> BEVERLY HILLS, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Litton Industries Inc. said it received a $20 million contract to design and install an automated storage and retrieval system at General Motors Corp.'s metal fabrication plant in Grand Rapids, Mich.    Litton, a diversified electronics concern, said it expects the system to be completed by the spring of 1988. </TEXT></DOC>